Reviews.Title: For the money...
Reviews.Author: Joseph Sprague
Reviews.Content: It's decent. I got a sweet deal on this laptop about a year ago. It does its job. Windows 8 is pretty annoying on a laptop, but that's neither here nor there I guess. As far as the physical attributes go, it's slim and light, although it feels a little cheap and plastic. It's slowed down quite a bit in the last year, and the battery life's deteriorated quite a bit. But it still does everything I need it to. So if you're looking for a basic laptop for a decent price, this is a pretty good choice.

Reviews.Title: a great buy!
Reviews.Author: William Smith
Reviews.Content: This was purchased as a travel computer to replace lugging around a heavier laptop. Turns out it is everything and more than I expected. The only minor complaint would be that the battery only lasts about three hours.

Reviews.Title: HP computer runs well
Reviews.Author: Mysterious Reviewer
Reviews.Content: UPDATE JAN 8: The mouse on this keyboard is less than nimble. I find it hard to use the mouse as I need to press down hard to get a response. I have swapped to USB ported Logitech mouse as I get a better response. It is also less tiring to use for my older hands and fingers.UPDATE DEC 29: HP flashed the bios and the computer arrived Dec 28. To say Windows 8 is different would be an understatement. Windows 8 is very different. It boots, but, like Vista, it contains too many new ideas, and not enough is explained to the user on how to use this new operating system. Having to use Windows 8 gets headachy real fast. My daughter plans to install Linux Mint and teach me how to use it. I guess that says it all.As to HP: Their tech support and customer service was outstanding once the problem was found. HP arranged for FedEx to pick and return the computer. Due to the holidays there was an understandable repair delay but the day after Christmas the HP Pavilion Sleekbook was repaired and shipped back. I was very pleased with HP's technical support.UPDATE DEC 13: Today, the system restore disk arrived and we attempted to perform system restore. That failed. Contacted HP Support and discovered the computer OS could not authenticate the Windows product key (something new to Windows 8) and the laptop will have to be returned to HP so the techs can "flash" the bios and re-inject the product key into the Motherboard as the HP Pavilion laptop uses UEFI to boot. HP will send a pre-addressed shipping label and mailing box so we can return the computer for repair. This repair normally takes about two weeks but should be a bit longer due to the holidays, according to the HP Tech. Will update this review once the laptop is repaired and running.UPDATE DEC 11: Called HP Support after checking the order status that stated the System Recovery disk delivery date was movedto DEC 28. The promised disk was supposed to arrive DEC 5 then DEC 12. Now the delivery was moved to DEC 28. According to HP, the System Recovery Disk is in "short supply". It would have been nice if HP had stated this at the start rather than leading me to believe the recovery disk was going to be sent DEC 5 and so forth. IF the disk arrives DEC 28, this means I will have had this computer for about a month before being able to use it.UPDATE DEC 11: With no signs of shipment or delivery of the System Restore Disk, I contacted HP this morning. HP promised to have the shipment status updated within the next four hours and to ship the recovery disk. I will update this review when needed.UPDATE DEC 7: The expected delivery of the System Restore disk was moved to DEC 12. I am still awaiting the delivery of the restore disk so we can try out the computer.I looked forward to trying and reviewing the HP Pavillion 14-inch laptop Sleekbook and today the computer arrived. I was disappointed as the laptop arrived with a non-operating Windows 8 OS. I called HP tech support, and spent almost 1 1/2 hours as they tried to get the computer to work, before HP tech support decided to send a free Windows 8 System Restore thumb drive. I will then reinstall the OS and hopefully the computer will work.Needless to say I am a bit disappointed as I looked forward to trying and using the new laptop that features Windows 8.HP tech support was excellent and they did their best to help.I will update this review after I am able to use the HP Pavillion Sleekbook computer.

Reviews.Title: It's freakin' awesome.
Reviews.Author: Samuel
Reviews.Content: First of all let me start off that this is a budget laptop, but it's still freakin' awesome. At first I felt overwhelmed with the start page, making the jump from my Compaq Windows Xp to Windows 8 was quite an experience. But right off the get go I fooled around with the apps, got my e-mail set up, messenger, and my desktop just the way I want it and BAM! This laptop became my home.I use this everywhere! At the diner, at work, home by my bed, and even in the toilet watching my anime.If I let it load it can stream the 1080 HD! Clear and smooth...Look, I bought this laptop for five reasons;1-To watch Netflix.(OH! the app is already pre-loaded!)2-To watch Hulu.3-To watch Crunchyroll.4- To read the news, (FANTASTIC APP FOR THAT TOO!)5- And to participate in a variety of social medias.For all this reasons, it's mega-awesome.Now, the things I don't like.Microsoft Word is crap.Paint is crap.In fact, many basic windows tools that are free in XP are either crap, or you have to pay for them. Yes you heard me, they have found a way to monetize simple basic tools that were awesome and free in XP. Thank god for Google, the internet, and fellow nerds who devote their time posting freeware. I love you Google.Besides the greedy HP jerks trying to monetize EVERYTHING, this laptop, is awesome.That is all._Samuel. :]

Reviews.Title: Very slow, hardly good enough to play minecraft with... Hard drive failed 37 days after purchase
Reviews.Author: Anderson Silva
Reviews.Content: Currently on hold with HP support trying to see if they can send me a new hard drive. I will never buy a pavilion again. It is not the first time I've had poor quality components from this line of laptops.Update 2013-02-27: I have been contacted by HP Customer Service after giving them a 1 star review here. I told them how bad my experience was with their customer service. They have extended the warranty of my less than 45 day old laptop, which I appreciate, but I also hope they will take the feedback I've given and work with their off-site technical support to do a better job.I am still leaving the product with 1 star as I am not satisfied with the product itself, but HP as a service provider has stepped up to it for me.
